ohan’s musical Little Johnny Jones and Ernest Hemingway’s short story “My Old Man.” The book is also much more-a fascinating cultural history that illuminates the history of horse racing and betting, the democratization of sport, changing conceptions of masculinity, the hypocrisy of Victorian morality, the lionizing and demonizing of celebrities, and a variety of other inviting topics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJockeyszEnglandvBiography. 0aJockeyszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Sports.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013494040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300134940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300134940/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles